club_des: Irons are categorized by numbers, with each number indicating a different loft angle. A lower-numbered iron (like a 3-iron) has a lower loft, resulting in longer distances and a lower trajectory, while a higher-numbered iron (like a 9-iron) has a higher loft, producing shorter distances with a high ascent.
